# rule.require.isolated-cli-subpath-exports

every cli command must have isolated export subpath. aggregated `/cli` loads all modules = OOM.

## pattern

| operation | needs brain? | import path |
|-----------|--------------|-------------|
| route.* | no | `pkg/cli/route` |
| review | yes | `pkg/cli/review` |
| reflect | yes | `pkg/cli/reflect` |

## fix

package.json:
```json
"exports": { "./cli/route": "...", "./cli/review": "...", "./cli/reflect": "..." }
```

shell:
```bash
# bad: import('pkg/cli') — loads ALL
# good: import('pkg/cli/route') — loads only route
```

## symptoms

OOM on simple ops, slow startup, memory spikes before work

## enforcement

violation = **BLOCKER**
